	<a id="top"></a>
	
	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">DesigningCollaborativeWorkspaces</h1>
	<div id="bodyContent">
		<h3 id="siteSub">From SPA Wiki</h3>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="index.php?title=DesigningCollaborativeWorkspaces#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="index.php?title=DesigningCollaborativeWorkspaces#searchInput">search</a></div>
		<!-- start content -->
<p>In this workshop we used modelling workspaces with lego people, clay and cardboard to discuss factors which impede collaboration and support collaboration.
</p><p><b>What Impedes Collaboration?</b>
</p>
<ul><li> Interruptions
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> Smells (smoke, food)
</li><li> Noise (phones, chatter, music)
</li><li> Movement (people walking thru)
</li><li> Visual (TV or views out of window - helicopter, gymnast, etc)
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Furniture
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> Inset desk
</li><li> Unadjustable/rigid furniture
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Distance between team members
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> slows down questioning
</li><li> tea/coffee/toilet food
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Collaboration tools
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> No whiteboards
</li><li> No wallspace
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Environment
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> Heat/cold - no control
</li><li> Bright lights (glare or dim)
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<p><b>What supports Collaboration?</b>
</p>
<ul><li> Appropriate proximity of desks - close enough for osmotic communication but not too close.
</li><li> Team cocoon/boundary
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> minimize interruptions from outside
</li><li> amplify communication inside
</li><li> ownership of the space
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Flexibility
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> furniture that can be reconfigured
</li><li> spare desks and space
</li><li> movable walls, whiteboards
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Meeting rooms
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> several spaces
</li><li> big room for planning and smaller breakout rooms
</li><li> rooms that you can program in - network connection
</li><li> whiteboards
</li><li> glass walls?
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Lunch space/cafeteria
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> Communal space but not too big - connect with other teams
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>
<ul><li> Quiet soace
</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li> make private phonecalls (can be small meeting room if available enough)
</li></ul>
</dd></dl>

